Label: 'body length without tail'
Text definition: The length of the body that includes the tail
Annotations: IAO:0000119 "Ansell,  W. F. H. (1965). Standardisation of Field Data on Mammals. Zoologica Africana, 1(1) 97-113. doi: 10.1080/00445096.1965.11447303"

Label: 'ear length'
Annotations: IAO:0000119 "Ansell,  W. F. H. (1965). Standardisation of Field Data on Mammals. Zoologica Africana, 1(1) 97-113. doi: 10.1080/00445096.1965.11447303"

Label: 'full body length'
Text definition: The length of the body that includes the tail
Annotations: IAO:0000119 "Ansell,  W. F. H. (1965). Standardisation of Field Data on Mammals. Zoologica Africana, 1(1) 97-113. doi: 10.1080/00445096.1965.11447303"

Label: 'hind foot length with claw'
Text definition: The length of a hind foot that includes a cutaneous appendage
Equivalent to: 'length' and ('inheres in' some 'pes' and ('has part' some 'cutaneous appendage'))
Annotations: IAO:0000119 "Ansell,  W. F. H. (1965). Standardisation of Field Data on Mammals. Zoologica Africana, 1(1) 97-113. doi: 10.1080/00445096.1965.11447303"

Label: 'length line from helix of outer ear to intertragus incisure'
Equivalent to: 'length' and ('inheres in' some 'line from helix of outer ear to intertragus incisure')
Annotations: IAO:0000119 "Ansell,  W. F. H. (1965). Standardisation of Field Data on Mammals. Zoologica Africana, 1(1) 97-113. doi: 10.1080/00445096.1965.11447303"

Label: 'line from helix of outer ear to intertragus incisure'
Subclass of: 'anatomical line' AND 'connects' some 'helix of outer ear' AND 'connects' some 'intertragic incisure'
Annotations: IAO:0000119 "Ansell,  W. F. H. (1965). Standardisation of Field Data on Mammals. Zoologica Africana, 1(1) 97-113. doi: 10.1080/00445096.1965.11447303"

Label: 'vertebrate organism'
Text definition: An individual organism that belongs to the group Vertebrata.
Comments: to be replaced by term from NCBI_taxon

Label: 'vertebrate trait observing process'
Text definition: An observing process that measures a trait of a vertebrate organism. May measure an actual organism or an image of an organism.
Equivalent to: 'observing process' and ('has_specified_input' some 'vertebrate organism') and ('has_specified_output' some 'measurement datum')
